bilingual.source: Say where you went and who you went with.
bilingual.target: 说出你去了哪里和你和谁一起去的。
博比和他的爸爸在一起。

bilingual.source: Here I am with my deskmate David.
bilingual.target: 这是我和我的同桌大卫。

list.abstract: 《With》是梅艳芳于2002年3月16日由Universal Music Ltd.发行的粤语流行歌曲专辑，共收录10首歌曲。 该专辑是中国香港歌手梅艳芳第21张粤语专辑，也是梅艳芳生前最后一张个人音乐专辑。 该专辑为纪念梅艳芳加盟乐坛20周年的大碟，当中收录了多首梅艳芳与11位好友合唱的歌曲，包括张国荣、张学友、谭咏麟、许志安、王菲、陈慧琳等等。
《With》是香港歌手梅艳芳第21张粤语专辑，也是梅艳芳生前最后一张个人音乐专辑，2002年由正东唱片发行。 这只为纪念梅艳芳加盟乐坛20周年的大碟，当中收录了多首梅艳芳与11位好友合唱的歌曲，包括张国荣、张学友、谭咏麟、许志安、王菲、陈慧琳等等。

yingyinNormal.en: Nowhere, with no one doing nothing with nobody.
yingyinNormal.zh: 不在任何地方，没和任何人在一起，没和任何人做任何事。

yingyinNormal.en: Dance with you? He didn't even speak to you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 和你跳舞？他都没和你说过话。

yingyinNormal.en: Yes, but a war with who?
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，和谁开战？

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna stick with them.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想和他们在一起

yingyinNormal.en: Break up with Charlie. What?
yingyinNormal.zh: 和查莉分手吧！

yingyinNormal.en: Hello, it's Mummy Rabbit with Rebecca and Richard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你好，我们是兔妈妈和瑞贝卡和理查德。

yingyinNormal.en: Peppa and George are at the playground with their friends.
yingyinNormal.zh: 佩琪和乔治和朋友们在游乐场里玩。

yingyinNormal.en: How was your date with Joey?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你和乔伊的约会怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: I really like talking with you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我挺喜欢和你聊天的。

yingyinNormal.en: I've been rehearsing with Kelsi.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我在和凯西彩排过了。

yingyinNormal.en: What does that have to do with me?
yingyinNormal.zh: 这和我有什么关系？

yingyinNormal.en: So, why are you trying with me?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你为什么还要和我说？

yingyinNormal.en: You didn't see him dance with me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你没见他和我跳舞了吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I've discussed it with my staff.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我已经和我手下讨论过了。

yingyinNormal.en: Good. Riley. Nothing to do with me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 很好 莱丽，和我没关系。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you in contact with your brother?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你和你哥哥还有联系吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Haymitch. I'm with the Mockingjay.
yingyinNormal.zh: 黑密斯呢？我和嘲笑鸟一样。

yingyinNormal.en: Yeah. Singing with you felt like that.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，和你唱歌就象那样。

yingyinNormal.en: Hang on. You've spent time with Amy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 先别走，你和Amy相处过。

yingyinNormal.en: But history has nothing to do with us.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可是历史已逝，和我们无关。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: accompanied by another person or thing

examination_example.sentence: "We see that the program is associated <highlight>with</highlight> a 30 percent reduction in deforestation," Ferraro says.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 费拉罗说:“我们看到该计划与森林砍伐减少30%有关。”

examination_example.sentence: A native literary drama had been created, its alliance <highlight>with</highlight> the public playhouses established.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一部本土的文学戏剧已经诞生，它与公共剧场的联盟已经建立。

examination_example.sentence: Hugging protects people who are under stress from the increased risk for colds that's usually associated <highlight>with</highlight> stress.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拥抱可以保护压力下的人，避免因压力而增加的感冒风险。

examination_example.sentence: When companies get into trouble <highlight>with</highlight> the law, evidence of good character can win them a less costly punishment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当公司触犯法律时，良好品行的证据可以为他们换来代价更低的惩罚。

examination_example.sentence: If you discontinue it, you're going to have your most loyal customers really upset <highlight>with</highlight> you.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你停止它，你将会让你最忠实的顾客对你非常不满。

examination_example.sentence: If you are unfamiliar <highlight>with</highlight> words or idioms, you guess at their meaning, using clues presented in the context.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果你不熟悉单词或习语，你可以根据上下文中出现的线索猜测它们的意思。

sense_info_list.en: possessing as a feature or accompaniment

examination_example.sentence: Merely helping a gift-giver gain access to other officials, unless done <highlight>with</highlight> clear intent to pressure those officials, is not corruption.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 仅仅帮助送礼者接触其他官员，除非有明确的向这些官员施压的意图，否则不算腐败。

examination_example.sentence: Firms seem to invest more in places where most people are relatively happy, rather than in places <highlight>with</highlight> happiness inequality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 公司似乎会在大多数人相对幸福的地方投资更多，而不是在幸福不平等的地方。

examination_example.sentence: A typical work consists of a single beautiful black-and-white photograph taken on an epic walk, <highlight>with</highlight> the mileage and number of days taken listed beneath.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个典型的作品包括一张在史诗般的徒步旅行中拍摄的黑白照片，下面列出了拍摄的里程和天数。

examination_example.sentence: It is deeply uncomfortable – it's the emotional equivalent of wearing a jacket weighted <highlight>with</highlight> stones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这让人非常不舒服——这就像穿了一件石头做的夹克。

examination_example.sentence: Other industries are recruiting them <highlight>with</highlight> similar or better pay.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 其他行业在以类似或更高的薪酬招聘他们。

examination_example.sentence: Unfortunately, people create inner barriers <highlight>with</highlight> a help of exaggerating fears.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不幸的是，人们通过夸大恐惧来制造内心的障碍。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>With</highlight> gyms and in-person exercise classes off-limits to many people these days, it can be tricky to know where to start.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如今，很多人都不去健身房，也不参加健身课程，所以很难知道从哪里开始。

examination_example.sentence: In the absence of work, a society designed <highlight>with</highlight> other ends in mind could disturb strikingly different circumstances for the future of labor and leisure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在没有工作的情况下，一个为其他目的而设计的社会可能会扰乱劳动和休闲的未来截然不同的情况。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>With</highlight> so much focus on children's use of screens, it's easy for parents to forget about their own screen use.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 因为如此关注孩子对屏幕的使用，家长很容易忘记自己对屏幕的使用。

examination_example.sentence: Unexpected results have two benefits: you pretty quickly learn to deal <highlight>with</highlight> disappointment and realize that when one door closes, another opens.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 意想不到的结果有两个好处:你很快学会处理失望，并意识到当一扇门关闭时，另一扇门会打开。

examination_example.sentence: Australia deals <highlight>with</highlight> the unjustified dismissal paradox by excluding employees earning above a specified "high-income threshold".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 澳大利亚通过排除收入超过特定“高收入门槛”的员工来处理不合理解雇悖论。

examination_example.sentence: All the daily business has been promptly dealt <highlight>with</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 所有日常事务都得到了及时处理。

sense_info_list.en: indicating the manner or attitude of the person

examination_example.sentence: Nine holes of golf once a week <highlight>with</highlight> short walks on other days.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 每周打一次九洞高尔夫球，其他时间进行短途散步。

examination_example.sentence: Thankfully, there are signs that this is already happening, <highlight>with</highlight> Generation Z seeking to learn from their millennial predecessors.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 庆幸的是，有迹象表明这已经发生了，Z世代正在寻求向他们的千年前辈学习。

examination_example.sentence: Divorced persons are viewed <highlight>with</highlight> some disapproval.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大家对离婚的人有些不满。

examination_example.sentence: John Brunnquell would disagree <highlight>with</highlight> Julie Stanton over regenerative products' markets prospects.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 约翰·布伦奎尔不同意朱莉·斯坦顿对再生产品市场前景的看法。

examination_example.sentence: According to Paragraph 1, museums are faced <highlight>with</highlight> difficulties in maintaining their plastic items.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据第1段，博物馆在维护其塑料物品方面面临困难。

examination_example.sentence: According to the last paragraph, a key to coping <highlight>with</highlight> dark patterns is businesses' self-discipline.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据最后一段，应对黑暗模式的关键是企业的自律。

examination_example.sentence: As a zoology professor, I agree <highlight>with</highlight> Emma Marris that zoo displays can be sad and cruel.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作为一名动物学教授，我同意艾玛·马里斯的观点，即动物园的展览可能是悲伤和残忍的。

examination_example.sentence: You also quickly learn to adapt and come up <highlight>with</highlight> creative solutions to the problems the painting presents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你还可以很快学会适应并想出创造性的解决方案来解决绘画中出现的问题。

examination_example.sentence: In fact, evidence shows that most dogs stay <highlight>with</highlight> one partner their whole lives.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，有证据表明，大多数狗一生都和一个伴侣在一起。

examination_example.sentence: When you compare your current status <highlight>with</highlight> the starting point, you'll find you've made progress.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当你把你现在的状态和最开始的时候相比时，你会发现你已经取得了进步。

examination_example.sentence: She was unwilling to make friends <highlight>with</highlight> workmates.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 她不愿意和同事交朋友。

sense_info_list.en: possessing as a feature or accompaniment

examination_example.sentence: Teachers <highlight>with</highlight> a multicultural background or training could perhaps overcome such curriculum challenges, but they're few and far between.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 拥有多元文化背景或受过培训的教师也许能克服这样的课程挑战，但这样的老师少之又少。

examination_example.sentence: We would live in a large two-story house <highlight>with</highlight> floors and the staircase made of wood.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们将住在一栋两层的大房子里，有地板和木制楼梯。

examination_example.sentence: People <highlight>with</highlight> HSAM often have to make efforts to avoid focusing on the past.
examination_example.sentence_trans: HSAM（超忆症）患者通常必须努力避免关注过去。

examination_example.sentence: It supplies the body <highlight>with</highlight> enough calories.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它为身体提供足够的卡路里。

examination_example.sentence: They provide residents <highlight>with</highlight> the resources needed.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们为居民提供所需的资源。

examination_example.sentence: I'll pay <highlight>with</highlight> my credit card.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我用信用卡付账。

examination_example.sentence: One problem <highlight>with</highlight> these sources is that the deep water also has a higher level of salt than shallower aquifers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些水源的一个问题是深层水比浅层水含盐量更高。

examination_example.sentence: They would be unpopular <highlight>with</highlight> drivers who only trust their own skills.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们不会受到那些只相信自己技术的司机的欢迎。

examination_example.sentence: What is the problem <highlight>with</highlight> many companies according to news report?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据新闻报道，许多公司存在什么问题？

examination_example.sentence: "Being taller is associated <highlight>with</highlight> longer life expectancy, " he said.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他说：“身高越高，预期寿命越长。”

examination_example.sentence: The figures include a number of costs associated <highlight>with</highlight> air pollution.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些数字包括了与空气污染有关的一些成本。

examination_example.sentence: Lunch boxes have evolved along <highlight>with</highlight> the transformation of schools.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 午餐盒随着学校的转型而发展。

examination_example.sentence: Crafts like knitting and crocheting may help to keep off a decline in brain function <highlight>with</highlight> age.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 编织和钩编等手工艺可能有助于防止大脑功能随着年龄的增长而下降。

examination_example.sentence: The road was frozen <highlight>with</highlight> snow.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 道路被雪冻住了。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>With</highlight> the exception of South Africa, the only light rail metro system in sub-Saharan Africa is in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 除南非外，撒哈拉以南非洲唯一的轻轨地铁系统位于埃塞俄比亚的亚的斯亚贝巴。

examination_example.sentence: I have made rapid progress in my math since you shared your good experience <highlight>with</highlight> me.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自从你和我分享了你的好经验，我的数学进步很快。

examination_example.sentence: My time at the restaurant will remain <highlight>with</highlight> me forever and benefit (使受益) me in the future.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我在餐馆的时光将永远伴随着我，并使我在未来受益。

examination_example.sentence: If Alice follows the advice, I think she will get on well <highlight>with</highlight> her mother.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 如果爱丽丝听从建议，我想她会和她妈妈相处得很好。

examination_example.sentence: The writer used the ways of dealing <highlight>with</highlight> waste bottles as an example to support the idea.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 作者用处理废瓶子的方法为例来支持这一观点。

examination_example.sentence: Points were awarded for part-time jobs, housework, effort in school, and ability to deal <highlight>with</highlight> problems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 兼职工作、家务、在学校的努力和处理问题的能力都会得到加分。

examination_example.sentence: Learning has nothing to do <highlight>with</highlight> doing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 学习与行动无关。

examination_example.sentence: Chile (智利) is a long and beautiful country <highlight>with</highlight> ocean to the west and mountains to the east.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 智利是一个狭长而美丽的国家，西面是海洋，东面是山脉。

examination_example.sentence: When someone without a medical degree sees a flagged result <highlight>with</highlight> no explanation on the website, there's room for all kinds of stories to form in their minds—and also great worry.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当一个没有医学学位的人在网站上看到一个没有任何解释的标记结果时，他们的脑海中会形成各种各样的故事——还有巨大的担忧。

examination_example.sentence: One interesting activity is for the British to enjoy the fun photos <highlight>with</highlight> short stories behind.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一个有趣的活动是让英国人欣赏有趣的照片，后面还有小故事。

examination_example.sentence: The field is covered <highlight>with</highlight> snow.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 田野被雪覆盖着。

examination_example.sentence: He has tested robots <highlight>with</highlight> different patients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他用不同的病人测试了机器人。

examination_example.sentence: To encourage Alex to surprise himself <highlight>with</highlight> a new game.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 为了鼓励亚历克斯去用一个新游戏给自己一个惊喜。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>With</highlight> the development of China, our government is more and more enthusiastic about protecting the environment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着中国的发展，我们的政府越来越热衷于保护环境。

examination_example.sentence: The princess slammed the door in the frog's face <highlight>with</highlight> a big BANG.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着砰的一声，公主在青蛙面前把门关上了。

examination_example.sentence: The scientists said this and a related species, which are grouped together under the name Myotis, had telomeres that did not shorten <highlight>with</highlight> age.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家们表示，这种蝙蝠以及相关物种都属于鼠耳蝠属，它们的端粒不会随着年龄而缩短。

examination_example.sentence: People <highlight>with</highlight> health problems go online to look for the new treatment.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 有健康问题的人上网寻找新的治疗方法。

examination_example.sentence: The rise of social networking has made it easier for people <highlight>with</highlight> uncommon diseases to connect <highlight>with</highlight> each other and feel less alone.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 社交网络的兴起使患有罕见疾病的人更容易相互联系，感觉不那么孤独。

sense_info_list.zh: 伴着; 带着(声音/手势/表情)

examination_example.sentence: Our school has put up a sign at the gate, saying "Greet your child <highlight>with</highlight> a smile, not a mobile".
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们学校在大门口立了一块牌子，上面写着“用微笑迎接孩子，不要用手机”。

examination_example.sentence: John was greeted <highlight>with</highlight> a kiss.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 迎接约翰的是一个吻。

examination_example.sentence: What's more, she was always patient <highlight>with</highlight> her customers.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 而且，她对顾客总是很有耐心。

examination_example.sentence: Mr.Brown is a teacher who is strict <highlight>with</highlight> all his students.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 布朗先生是一位对自己的所有学生都很严格的老师。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>With</highlight> a little hard work, you can learn to communicate better <highlight>with</highlight> your parents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 稍加努力，你就能学会更好地与父母沟通。

word_usage.usage: with和by两者都可表示某人怎么去做某事，只是使用的途径不同。使用by时，多半指通过某一种行为去得到结果，而with则是通过使用某种工具或者物体去得到结果。
